      public void checkIfEnoughSpaceInColumn(int cardsNumber, int column) throws NoSpaceEnoughInShelfColumnException
      This method checks if a list of object cards, taken by a player from the board, can be added to a shelf.
      Parameters:
      cardsNumber - the number of card to insert in the column.
      column - column where a player wants to insert his object cards.
      Throws:
      NoSpaceEnoughInShelfColumnException

    • checkIfEnoughSpace

      public void checkIfEnoughSpace(int cardsNumber) throws NoSpaceEnoughInShelfException

      Parameters:
      cardsNumber - the number of tiles
      Throws:
      NoSpaceEnoughInShelfException - if there is no space in the shelf for the tiles
